Package net.hudup.core.logistic

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LineProcessor
    Any class implementing this interface must define the main method LineProcessor.process(String) to specify how to process a line string.
    RatingFilter
    This interface, called rating filter specifies how to select (filter) a rating value based on comparing such rating value with a referred rating value.
    Runner
    This interface specifies that any object that implements it can start, pause, resume, and stop by itself.
    UriAssoc
    This interface proposes rules (methods) processing on objects identified by Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) as normal file when URI refers to any resource on net system.
    UriFilter
    This interface is used to select an object identified with a URI according to some custom criteria.
    UriProcessor
    This interface is used for processing some task on specified URI.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractRunner
    This class is a runner that implements partially the interface Runner.
    Cipher
    This utility class provides methods of encryption and dercyption.
    ClipboardUtil
    This class provides utility methods to process on clip-board such as getting text from clip-board and setting text to clip-board.
    DSUtil
    This final class provides utility static methods for processing data structures such as asserting, conversion, parsing, splitting, processing, etc.
    Dual
    This utility class represents a pair of values represented by its two variables Dual.one and Dual.other.
    I18nUtil
    This final utility class provides utilit methods for internationalization (I18n) for different languages.
    ListMap<K,V>
    This class implements the Map interface whose keys are copied in another ListSet.
    ListSet<E>
    This class implements the Set interface but its elements are stored in the internal list ListSet.list.
    MathUtil
    This final class provides utility static methods for mathematics such as summing, taking logarithm, powering, formatting, rounding, vector operators, matrix operators, etc.
    MinMax
    This utility class contains a minimum value and maximum value.
    NetUtil
    This final class provides utility static methods for network programming.
    RunnerThread
    This class is the thread to start a runnable object called Runner.
    SystemUtil
    Utility class for system tasks.
    UriAdapter
    This class is also a URI associator because it implements the interface UriAssoc but it hides all physical systems and protocols (file system, compressed file, HTTP, database, etc.).
    UriAdapter.AdapterReader
    This class is the Reader (for reading operations on archives identified by URI) with support of URI adapter UriAdapter.
    UriAdapter.AdapterWriteChannel
    This class is the ByteChannel (for both writing and reading operations on archives identified by URI) with support of URI adapter UriAdapter.
    UriAdapter.AdapterWriter
    This class is the Writer (for writing operations on archives identified by URI) with support of URI adapter UriAdapter.
    UriAssocAbstract
    This class is the abstract URI associator which defines most of simple methods of the interface UriAssoc.
    ValueTriple
    This class represents a triple which has one integer key ValueTriple.key and two double values such as ValueTriple.value1 and ValueTriple.value2.
    Vector
    This class represents a vector of double values.
    xSubURI
    This class is similar to xURI except that the scheme inside the path of xSubURI is simplest.
    xURI
    This class is a wrapper of URI.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HudupException
    This class represents exception occurred in Hudup framework.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    BaseClass
    This annotation indicates that the attached class is base class.
    Composite
    This annotation indicates a composite class.
    NextUpdate
    This annotation indicates that the attached class represents a next-update algorithm.
